            <title>[SPARK-23328] Disallow default value None in na.replace/replace when &apos;to_replace&apos; is not a dictionary</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23328</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We happened to set &lt;tt&gt;None&lt;/tt&gt; as a default value via &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-19454&quot; title=&quot;Improve DataFrame.replace API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-19454&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-19454&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which is quite weird.&lt;br/&gt;
Looks we better only do this when the input is dictionary.&lt;br/&gt;
